4. **Active Baseline** (v2 heritage) — the existing 3 cards (Identity & Vibe, Evolution State, Operating Directives) reading from `@/lib/soul`.\n- The chat's `src/app/chat/page.tsx` is **unchanged** — its `import { SOUL_PROMPT } from \"@/lib/soul\"` continues to read the build-time canonical persona per LESSON-018.\n- `npm run build` (output: `\"export\"`) succeeds; `?raw` webpack rule for `.md` files remains unchanged.\n\n### Root Cause\n\nFID-006 v2 anchored to the **consumer side** of the soul system (the disk-resident `SOUL.md` reader at `registry.rs:192` + the `ContextAssembler.assemble_system_prompt` section format) and built a viewer of the artifact. The **producer side** (the `ControlFrame::SoulManifest` dispatch + `generate_template_soul` template) was the missing piece. This FID closes the gap.\n\n### Evidence\n\n> **Pasteback rule (LESSON-016).** Every claim about savant-orig below has (1) a fenced `grep -rn <symbol> <path>` or 3+ line `sed -n '<start>,<end>p' <file>` excerpt; (2) a one-line claim-equivalence self-check immediately after; (3) a Loop-0 diff loop-line in §Perfection Loop. PB-1..PB-10 are the v2 pastebacks — they remain **kept** because the v2 file-resident infrastructure is faithful to savant-orig canon. PB-A..PB-G are the v3 additions — they cover the actual builder chain.\n\n#### PB-1..PB-10 (carried from v2 — \"kept\" — file-resident persona infrastructure)\n\n> **Note.** The full pasteback evidence for PB-1..PB-10 lives in [`dev/fids/archive/FID-2026-07-13-006-v2-soul-manifest-and-workspace-scaffold.md` §Evidence]. They are summarized here as \"kept\" because (a) the v2 implementation is verified by 4 AUDIT gates PASS (tsc exit 0, `npm run build` 16/16 pages, prettier clean, FID-151 grep gate 2 consumers), (b) `code-reviewer-minimax-m3` APPROVE on all 6 criteria, and (c) Spencer ratified the v2 file-resident infrastructure as part of Option B (\"keep the file-resident persona infrastructure (lib/soul.ts, raw.d.ts, webpack rule, workspac